le=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|&nbsp;\u2013\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\n|-\n| {{fb|TRI}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 15\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 7\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 6\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 24\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 15\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| +9\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 20\n|-\n| {{fb|TUR}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|&nbsp;\u2013\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n|-\n| {{fb|UKR}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 4\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| -4\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\n|-\n| {{fb|URU}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 9\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 6\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 11\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 16\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| -5\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 5\n|-\n| {{fb|USA}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 29\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 12\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 6\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 11\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 35\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 31\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| +4\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n| {{fb|VEN}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 8\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 4\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 7\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 8\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| -1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 6\n|-\n| {{fb|WAL}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 3\n|-\n| {{fb|YUG}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 3\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| -1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\n|-\n! Totals\n! 443\n! 190\n! 115\n! 138\n! 710\n! 564\n! +146\n! 500\n|}\n\n==Facts==\n* [[Costa Rica]] was the first (and so far the only) [[Central America]]n football team to win a game at a [[FIFA World Cup|World Cup]] tournament.\n* [[Costa Rica]] finished in first place in the [[1990 FIFA World Cup qualification]] and [[2002 FIFA World Cup qualification]] with the best punctuation in the history of the Hexagonal (23 pts).\n* [[Costa Rica]] is one of two ([[Cuba]] in [[1938 FIFA World Cup|1938]]) Central American or Caribbean squad ever to advance to the Quarter Finals of the [[FIFA World Cup]].\n\n==Kit history==\nCosta Rica wears traditionally a red jersey with blue shorts and white socks. Its away kit historically was a Juventus-style Black and White Striped Jersey with white shorts and white socks, due to these colors being the ones of CS La Libertad, one of the oldest clubs in Costa Rica. However, after 1997, the striped kit was replaced by a white kit with blue shorts. Starting in 2015, Boston based sportswear company [[New Balance]] will be the kit provider of the national team, taking over for Italian company [[Lotto Sport Italia|Lotto]].\n\n===Kit Suppliers===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Sponsor\n!Period\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|CRC}} [[Desport]] \n|1980\u20131989\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} [[Lotto Sport Italia|Lotto]]\n|1990\u20131994\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|GBR}} [[Reebok]]\n|1995\u20131999\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|Costa Rica}} Trooper\n|1999\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|MEX}} [[Atletica]]\n|2000\u20132001\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|Spain}} [[Joma]]\n|2002\u20132007\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} [[Lotto Sport Italia|Lotto]]\n|2007\u20132014\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|United States}} [[New Balance]]\n|2015\u2013present\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Association football|Costa Rica}}\n* [[Costa Rica national under-23 football team]]\n* [[Costa Rica national under-20 football team]]\n* [[Costa Rica national under-17 football team]]\n* [[Costa Rica at the FIFA World Cup]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Costa Rica national football team}}\n{{wikinews|Germany wins, 4\u20132 over Costa Rica in first World Cup match}}\n*[http://www.fedefutbol.com/ FEDEFUTBOL.com] - Website of the [[Costa Rican Football Federation]]\n*[https://www.fifa.com/associations/association=crc/ Costa Rica FIFA profile]\n*[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesc/cos-intres.html 1921 to 2009 Costa Rica match results] by ''Marcos Romero'' at [[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{succession box\n| before = Inaugural Champion\n| title  = [[CONCACAF Gold Cup|CONCACAF Champions]]\n| years  = [[1963 CONCACAF Championship|1963]] (First title)\n| after  = [[1965 CONCACAF Championship|1965]] {{fb-rt|MEX}}\n}}\n{{succession box\n| before = [[1967 CONCACAF Championship|1967]] {{fb-rt|GUA}}\n| title  = [[CONCACAF Gold Cup|CONCACAF Champions]]\n| years  = [[1969 CONCACAF Championship|1969]] (Second title)\n| after  = [[1971 CONCACAF Championship|1971]] {{fb-rt|MEX}}\n}}\n{{succession box\n| before = [[1985 CONCACAF Championship|1985]] {{fb-rt|CAN}}\n| title  = [[CONCACAF Gold Cup|CONCACAF Champions]]\n| years  = [[1989 CONCACAF Championship|1989]] (Third title)\n| after  = [[1991 CONCACAF Gold Cup|1991]] {{fb-rt|United States}}\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Costa Rica national football team}}\